    "text": "MENU\nNEWS BEST PICKS REVIEWS HOW-TO DEALS\nLAPTOPS WINDOWS\n.cls-1{fill:none;}.cls-2{clip-path:url(#clip-path);}.cls-3{clip-path:url(#clip-path-2);}.cls-4{fill:#fff;}\nHOT TOPICS Best laptops Best cheap laptops Laptop deals Best SSDs Best monitors\nWhat life and death taught me about digital memories\nAsrock X670E Taichi: This motherboard hits a sweet spot\nIs gigabit internet worth it? Only if you meet these 3 criteria\nLATEST STORIES\nNEWS\nGoogle Chrome can finally…search Chrome\nGoogle enables searches of your browsing history, open tabs, and bookmarks right from the Chrome address bar.\nBy Mark Hachman 10 hours ago\nBEST PICKS\nThe best free backup software and services: Where is it safe to skimp?\nThe best free backup software or online service balances good features with enough storage space to protect your valuable data. We've tested the major players so you can find the best one for you. Read on for our reviews.\nBy Jon Jacobi and Sam Singleton 14 hours ago\nNEWS\nSmuggler hides 202 Intel CPUs in a fake 'baby bump'\nA Chinese traveler was \"pregnant\" with tens of thousands of dollars worth of chips and phones\nBy Michael Crider 14 hours ago\nNEWS\nEven scalpers don't want the GeForce RTX 4080\nScalpers can't sell them, retailers don't want them back, and Nvidia may be forced into an early price cut for the GeForce RTX 4080.\nBy Michael Crider 15 hours ago\n0 seconds of 1 hour, 35 minutes, 50 seconds\n  DEAL\nThis Logitech wireless gaming mouse is fast, lightweight, and only $30\nThe Logitech G305 wireless gaming mouse is a fantastic pick for the budget-conscious buyer.\nBy Ashley Biancuzzo 15 hours ago\nBEST PICKS\nThe best gaming laptops under $1,000: Best overall, best battery life, and more\nThese are the best gaming laptops under $1,000 including popular brands such as Acer, HP, and Asus.\nBy Ashley Biancuzzo 15 hours ago\nUPDATED\nBest laptop deals: Top picks from budget to extreme\nThese are the best deals on laptops, notebooks, gaming laptops, and Chromebooks we can find, updated every weekday.\nBy Mark Hachman, Ian Paul and Ashley Biancuzzo 15 hours ago\nREVIEWS\nAsrock X670E Taichi review: This motherboard hits a sweet spot\nThe Asrock X670E Taichi packs a ton of capability into a sleek motherboard package that's surprisingly affordable.\nBy Thiago Trevisan 19 hours ago\nFEATURE\nWhat life and death taught me about digital memories\nThe death of my mother taught me that you have the best tool for remembering your loved ones right in your pocket. Use it.\nBy Mark Hachman 20 hours ago\nNEWS\nIntel's next-gen 'Meteor Lake' chip tech is ready now\nIntel's manufacturing chief says that the Intel 4 process that underpins Intel's next-gen Meteor Lake processor is manufacturing-ready, right now. Can Intel's 14th-gen Core chip be far behind?\nBy Mark Hachman 20 hours ago\nBEST PICKS\nThe fastest VPN: We identify the speediest performers\nIf you have the need, the need for VPN speed, we've got recommendations about the best choices for you.\nBy Ian Paul and Sam Singleton 2 days ago\nSPONSORED CONTENT\nNew Kinaxis HQ: The Right Notes for Success\nThe Kanata-based manufacturer of supply-chain management software has been riding a steady wave of growth during the pandemic as demand...\nSponsored by Kinaxis\nUPDATED\nBest PC computer deals: Top picks from desktops to all-in-ones\nWe've scoured the web to help you find the best deals on desktop PCs, gaming PCs, and all-in-one computers this December. Currently on discount: CyberPowerPC, HP, Skytech, and Apple.\nBy Sam Singleton 2 days ago\nNEWS\nYou can now play Sony's Spider-Man in first-person\nA new mod for Sony's Spider-Man remaster puts you behind the wall-crawler's mask — just don't try it right after lunch.\nBy Michael Crider 2 days ago\nNEWS\nChatGPT is the dazzling, scary future of AI chatbots\nChatGPT combines essay writing, WIkipedia, poetry and code analysis all into one. Check out this amazing (and free) AI text tool right now.\nBy Mark Hachman 2 days ago\nBEST PICKS\nBest portable power stations: Top picks for preparedness\nWhether you're the camping sort, or you live in an area prone to power outages, or you just like being prepared for anything, a power station that can charge all your devices is a must for your emergency arsenal. We've got some favorites to recommend.\nBy Jason Cipriani and Gordon Ung 2 days ago\nDEAL\nNab this powerful Lenovo ThinkPad laptop for 49% off\nThe Lenovo ThinkPadp X1 Carbon Gen 10 laptop is lightweight, fast, and 49% off.\nBy Ashley Biancuzzo 2 days ago\nNEWS\nSteam's most popular GPU isn't the one you think it is\nThe humble GeForce GTX 1650 is now sitting pretty at the top of Steam's user survey list.\nBy Michael Crider 2 days ago\nREVIEWS\nMSI MAG Z790 Tomahawk WiFi DDR4 review: Next-gen CPUs meet mainstream RAM\nThe MSI MAG Z790 Tomahawk WiFi DDR4 is an affordable motherboard with great I/O, plenty of M.2 slots, and a sleek design. But it lacks some of the next-gen features that will matter in the long term.\nBy Thiago Trevisan 2 days ago\nOPINION\nIs gigabit internet worth it? Only if you meet these 3 criteria\nDo you really need gigabit internet service? Probably not. Here's why it may be overkill, plus three scenarios where it actually makes sense.\nBy Jared Newman 2 days ago\nBEST DEALS\nBest Chromebook deals: Top picks from budget to midrange and more\nWe've scoured the web to help you find the best deals on Chromebooks this December. Currently on discount: Lenovo, Asus, HP, and Acer models.\nBy Sam Singleton 2 days ago\nMORE STORIES\n.cls-1{fill:none;}.cls-2{clip-path:url(#clip-path);}.cls-3{clip-path:url(#clip-path-2);}.cls-4{fill:#fff;}\nPCWorld helps you navigate the PC ecosystem to find the products you want and the advice you need to get the job done.\nPOLICIES\nPrivacy Policy\nCookie Policy\nMember Preferences\nEditorial independence\nLicensing & Eprints\nCalifornia: Do not Sell my Personal Info\nABOUT\nAbout Us\nAdvertise\nAd Choice\nContact Us\nFoundry Careers\nPCWORLD CATEGORIES\nBusiness\nLaptop\nMobile\nPC Hardware\nDeals\nSUBSCRIBE\nDigital Magazine - Subscribe\nManage Subscription\nGift Subscription\nNewsletters\n.cls-1{fill:#fff;}.cls-2{fill:none;}\nCopyright © 2022 IDG Communications, Inc.\n    Explore the Foundry Network +\n    Tech Advisor\nTech Hive\nMacworld\n    ",
